ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Treatment group
In the last 3 months, up to and including today, did you call someone to get professional counseling on the phone or by video chat for yourself?
In the last 3 months, how often did you get the professional counseling you needed on the phone or by video chat?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Sometimes; 3=Usually; 4=Always; 777=Not Applicable; 888=Don''t know; 999=Refuse. Not applicable indicates that the participant was not asked this question due to branching logic.

ElementDescription: In the last 3 months, did you need counseling or treatment right away?
In the last 3 months, up to and including today, when you needed counseling or treatment right away, how often did you see someone as soon as you wanted?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Sometimes; 3=Usually; 4=Always; 777=Not Applicable; 888=Don''t know; 999=Refuse. Not applicable indicates that the participant was not asked this question due to branching logic.

ElementDescription: In the last 3 months, not counting times you needed counseling or treatment right away, did you make any appointments for counseling or treatment?
In the last 3 months, not counting times you needed counseling or treatment right away, how often did you get an appointment for counseling or treatment as soon as you wanted?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Sometimes; 3=Usually; 4=Always; 777=Not Applicable; 888=Don''t know; 999=Refuse. Not applicable indicates that the participant was not asked this question due to branching logic.

ElementDescription: In the last 3 months, up to and including today, how often did the people you went to for counseling or treatment listen carefully to you?
In the last 3 months, up to and including today, how often did the people you went to for counseling or treatment explain things in a way you could understand?
In the last 3 months, up to and including today, how often did the people you went to for counseling or treatment show respect for what you had to say?
In the last 3 months, up to and including today, how often did the people you went to for counseling or treatment spend enough time with you?
In the last 3 months, up to and including today, how often did you feel safe when you were with the people you went to for counseling or treatment?
In the last 3 months, up to and including today, how often were you involved as much as you wanted in your counseling or treatment?

Using any number from 0 to 10, where 0 is the worst counseling or treatment possible and 10 is the best counseling or treatment possible, what number would you use to rate all your counseling or treatment in the last 3 months?
Notes: 0=Worst counseling or treatment possible; 10=Best counseling or treatment possible; 888=Don''t know; 999=Refuse
